The paper focuses on testing the consistency of DNN-based autonomous driving systems using GANs to generate accurate driving scenes. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for generating images, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the unsupervised framework, and machine learning (cs.LG) for the GANs. The testing is done on autonomous driving systems (cs.RO) and aims to improve their safety and reliability (cs.SY).
